Kenny saw spikes **while the per-draw blocking-Map probe was active**, and that probe reads the VB **position (offset 0) clean**. A per-draw GPU drain did NOT stop the live spike â†’ **NOT a timing/pipeline race**. So the GPU is reading **UNINITIALIZED memory that is NOT the position-at-offset-0 the probe checks** â€” bytes that are zero on replay, stale/garbage live.

