## 1. THE SYMPTOM (reframed 2026-06-07 â€” this is the key reframe)
Close, **soft-skinned** characters render with vertical "texture spikes": most of a draw's vertices collapse / fan out into thin shards. **It is NOT garment-specific** â€” Kenny confirmed it hits **Jawas (robes), dewbacks, and other creatures**. It is **DISTANCE-GATED**: far = clean, close = spikes. D3D9 (`gl05`) renders all of it clean. Flickers mildâ†”extreme frame to frame.

Distance gating == the LODâ†’skinning-mode switch (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1737`, chosen by on-screen size):
- far/tiny â†’ `SM_noSkinning`
- medium â†’ `SM_hardSkinning` (GPU skin, static-ish VB) â†’ **CLEAN**
- **close/large â†’ `SM_softSkinning`** â†’ CPU-skin into the shared dynamic VB ring every frame â†’ **BROKEN**

â‡’ The common factor is **the dynamic-ring soft-skin path itself**, not any mesh. THE WHOLE INVESTIGATION SHOULD BE FRAMED AROUND THE SOFT-SKIN DYNAMIC-RING PATH.

