codex
A key code path says if a skeleton joint has no resolver entry, the joint-to-root loop `continue`s, which means that array slot is not written by that frame’s loop. I’m checking whether mesh bone indices are remapped by name into this same skeleton/LOD ordering, because that determines whether a mesh can legally point at such a slot.
