**Provenance**

`transformArray` in soft skinning comes from the `Skeleton` for the shader primitive’s LOD:

- [SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:559>): `m_appearance.getSkeleton(m_lodIndex)`
- [SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:562>): `transformCount = skeleton.getTransformCount()`
- [SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:563>): `transformArray = skeleton.getBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()`

Callers of `skinData(...)` in this file:

- `prepareToDraw()` multi-stream path: [line 668](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:668>)
- `prepareToDraw()` direct dynamic path: [line 757](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:757>)
- `prepareToDraw()` system-to-dynamic path: [line 769](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:769>)
- `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()`: [line 934](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:934>)

`skinData()` dispatches soft skinning to `fillVertexBuffer()` at [line 1749](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1749>). There is no current `fillDynamicVertexBuffer(...)` symbol in this file; `fillVertexBuffer(...)` is the soft-skin fill path.

**Who owns/builds it**

The `Skeleton` owns the array:

- Members: `m_bindPoseModelToRootTransformBackingStore` / `m_bindPoseModelToRootTransforms` in [Skeleton.h](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.h:136>)
- Allocated in `Skeleton::allocateTransformArrays()` at [Skeleton.cpp:1865](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1865>), with `PoseModelTransform` storage allocated at [1892-1895](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1892>)
- `getBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()` forces/caches calculation for the frame at [Skeleton.cpp:1696](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1696>) and [1706-1709](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1706>)

The data is built from `jointToRoot * bindPoseModelToJoint`:

- `calculateBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()` starts at [Skeleton.cpp:1498](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1498>)
- It first calls `calculateJointToRootTransforms()` at [1521-1522](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1521>)
- It writes `m_bindPoseModelToRootTransforms[modelTransformIndex]` at [1535-1542](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1535>)

The animated components come from `TransformAnimationResolver`:

- `SkeletalAppearance2` owns `m_animationResolver`: [SkeletalAppearance2.h:417](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearance2.h:417>)
- Constructed at [SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1080](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1080>)
- Advanced each alter at [SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1474](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1474>)
- `Skeleton::calculateJointToRootTransforms()` asks resolver for components at [Skeleton.cpp:1414](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1414>)
- Resolver lazily evaluates an index if needed at [TransformAnimationResolver.cpp:687-699](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/controller/TransformAnimationResolver.cpp:687>)

**Can a valid index be stale/unfilled?**

Yes.

For normal mapped joints, the intended path fills each used joint once per frame, cached by frame number:

- joint-to-root cache guard: [Skeleton.cpp:1345-1350](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1345>)
- bind-pose-model-to-root cache guard: [Skeleton.cpp:1510-1515](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1510>)

But two valid-index holes exist:

1. If a joint has no resolver entry, `calculateJointToRootTransforms()` skips it with `continue` at [Skeleton.cpp:1404-1411](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1404>). Later `calculateBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()` still reads `m_jointToRootTransforms[modelTransformIndex]` for every joint at [1537-1542](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1537>). That can propagate stale or uninitialized `jointToRoot` into a valid `PoseModelTransform`.

2. `transformCount` includes hardpoints: [Skeleton.cpp:366-373](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:366>). `jointToRoot` hardpoints are filled at [1488-1489](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1488>), but `calculateBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()` explicitly does not support hardpoints yet and has only a TODO at [1546-1547](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1546>). A mesh skinning to a hardpoint name could get an in-range skeleton index whose `PoseModelTransform` entry is never written.

**transformCount semantics**

`transformCount` is the current `Skeleton::m_transformCount`, not the mesh’s referenced-bone count. It is built as the sum of current skeleton segment joint counts plus hardpoints:

- Constructor starts with root joint count: [Skeleton.cpp:768-770](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:768>)
- Rebuild recomputes via `Segment::transformCountAccumulate`: [Skeleton.cpp:1141](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:1141>)
- Accumulate includes `jointCount + hardpointCount`: [Skeleton.cpp:366-373](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/Skeleton.cpp:366>)

Mesh-local transform indices are remapped by name into this skeleton’s global transform ordering during mesh build:

- File-local transform names are looked up via `transformNameMap.findTransformIndex(...)`: [SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3760-3776](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3760>)
- If a mesh references a missing joint, the mesh is dropped: [3767-3772](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3767>)
- The remapped index is what gets stored in position weights: [3815-3817](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3815>)

**LOD / ordering**

A high-LOD mesh should not be using raw file-local bone ordering against a lower-LOD pose array. The mesh is rebuilt per LOD and its transform names are remapped through the skeleton transform name map for that LOD:

- `rebuildMesh(lodIndex)` chooses a skeleton for that LOD at [SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:2217-2220](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:2217>)
- It passes that skeleton’s `getTransformNameMap()` into `compositeMesh.addShaderPrimitives(...)`: [2252](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:2252>)
- `SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate` then creates `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive(..., lodIndex, ...)`: [SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3445](</mnt/d/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3445>)

So a simple “valid index but wrong ordering from another LOD” is not the expected path for a successfully built primitive. The LOD-sensitive failure that is plausible is different: high LOD may reference a joint name that resolves into the skeleton but that joint lacks a resolver entry or is a hardpoint/unhandled pose entry, producing an in-range but stale/uninitialized transform value.
